    {
      "id": "DLjHwaklhE7ezXWD9VgNf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1926.983902078812,
      "y": 339.61950836488415,
      "width": 416.9288330078125,
      "height": 320,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b31",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1513173129,
      "version": 2084,
      "versionNonce": 416854833,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776600406757,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Encoder Service\n- it dequeue's/Process message\n  from queue.\n- it generates multiple copies of\n   videos in multipe format eg\n  (480p, 720p, 1080p ...etc).\n- considering ABS ( Adaptive bitrate streaming)\n  we will use HLS protocol which will generate\n  .m3u8 manifest file & .ts file ( Video Segments)\n- .m3u8 file contains options that helps video player\n  to choose format according to network condition &\n  fetch that video segment to avoid buffering.\n- upload videos to blob storage \n    account & update metdata.\n- generate thumbnail for videos &\n   update bigtable & metadata with url.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Encoder Service\n- it dequeue's/Process message\n  from queue.\n- it generates multiple copies of\n   videos in multipe format eg\n  (480p, 720p, 1080p ...etc).\n- considering ABS ( Adaptive bitrate streaming)\n  we will use HLS protocol which will generate\n  .m3u8 manifest file & .ts file ( Video Segments)\n- .m3u8 file contains options that helps video player\n  to choose format according to network condition &\n  fetch that video segment to avoid buffering.\n- upload videos to blob storage \n    account & update metdata.\n- generate thumbnail for videos &\n   update bigtable & metadata with url.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "XoYRh77RequP31jkDF7CQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1566.8079198201497,
      "y": 720.3880208333335,
      "width": 364.88067626953125,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b32",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1817095337,
      "version": 2507,
      "versionNonce": 23072177,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776011051485,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Blob Storage\n- it stores raw video files, which \n  is ready to serve\n- we could have use distributed file\n  storage like HDFS, but managing blocks,\n  adding nodes(machines) & handling replication\n  across nodes would need to be manual so \n  scalabilty factor is challenging, but in \n  Blob storage it is been taken care already,\n  we just upload & fetch video files.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Blob Storage\n- it stores raw video files, which \n  is ready to serve\n- we could have use distributed file\n  storage like HDFS, but managing blocks,\n  adding nodes(machines) & handling replication\n  across nodes would need to be manual so \n  scalabilty factor is challenging, but in \n  Blob storage it is been taken care already,\n  we just upload & fetch video files.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "BYLFVhN8dt7XjtFFs1sEr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1562.8611965374978,
      "y": 1010.5473664416268,
